import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
import "bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="/src/styles/index.css">
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="main-section">
				<h1>Debugging My Mind ðŸ§ </h1>
				<p><strong>Welcome to my debugging zone</strong> a space where I share my personal journey exploring the fundamentals of Computer Science.</p>
				<p>My name is <strong>Jakxel</strong>, and I am currently studying Computer Systems Engineering at the Tijuana Institute of Technology. Through this blog, I want to document not only my achievements and discoveries but also the challenges and obstacles I encounter as I dive deeper into the world of programming, engineering, and technology.</p>
				<p>I often feel like what I study is not enough or that I am not making the necessary effort to truly understand the concepts I need. <strong>The real world demands dedication and constant effort</strong>, so this blog becomes a tool to complement my learning and delve deeper into my future as an engineer.</p>
			</section>
			
			<section class="second-section">
				<h2>Why debugging my mind?</h2>
				<p>  
					Just like debugging code, life sometimes requires us to "debug" our thoughts and habits. There are moments when we feel stuck or uncertain, but with patience and the right tools, we can work through these mental blocks. This blog is my effort to understand, improve, and growâ€”both in knowledge and mindset.
