			</section>
			
			<section class="third-section">
				<h3>My purpose</h3>
			<p>
				My goal is to build a solid foundation in Computer Science that will allow me to grow as a software engineer. I want to not only understand theory but also apply it in real-world projects. Through this blog, I will share my journey, mistakes, and discoveries with others who are on a similar path.
			</p>
			<p>
				Here, you'll find three main sections:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Core CS Fundamentals</strong>: Focused on key topics like algorithms, data structures, and programming principles.</li>
				<li><strong>Software Engineering & System Design</strong>: Practical insights into software development, system architecture, and design patterns.</li>
				<li><strong>Advanced Topics & Real-World Applications</strong>: Diving into emerging technologies like AI, machine learning, and more.</li>
			</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="fourth-section">
				<h2>A Continuous Journey</h2>
				<p>
					Learning is a non-linear process. There will be progress and setbacks, but each step is a chance to improve. I hope this blog inspires and encourages others as they debug their own minds and continue their learning journey.
				</p>
			</section>
			
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>